ssues with lye beads. Alas... the easiest solution was to use a fabric soft=
ener dryer sheet! Yes, it was that easy. I leave the same dryer sheet in wi=
th my bottles of lye in a plastic bag. I rub the dryer sheet on the bottle =
just before I pour it. I just keep using the same one. If it stops working,=
 I&amp;#039;ll get another dryer sheet to use. I&amp;#039;ve done dozens of=
 batches since then and that same dryer sheet has worked every time.<br>
<br>
